g.text: Manhattan is the borough with the highest number of zipcodes in the highest quintile of dog licenses
(656 - 2380 dogs), meaning it's the most dog-dense borough. Brooklyn follows Manhattan as the
borough with the second highest number of zipcodes in the highest quintile. Queens has the lowest
number of zipcodes in the highest quintile of dog licenses. Interestingly, people who live in Queens'
zipcodes closer to Long Island and with bigger yards hold the least dog licenses. The number
of dog licenses in Staten Island and the Bronx are in between Brooklyn and Queens.
